border: 3px solid black;}



to adjust margin(space b.w paragraph):
<style type="text/css">
	p {margin: 1px;}

</style>

<style type="text/css">
h4 { width: 350px;
height: 100px; }          (in gen we don't deal with height)
</style>

How to style links?  <a href="https://www.google.com">google</a>
One link has actually four different states:
<style type="text/css">
	a:link{color: red;
	       text-decoration: none;}                     (this sets default link)
	a:visited{color: green;}                            (tells whether link is previsited)
	a:hover{background-color: blue;                      (modifies hover properties)
	           text-decoration: underline;
	            font-weight: bold;}
	a:active{background-color: orange;}                   (holding mouse gives active state)
</style>

How to style more than one element at a time:
 <style type="text/css">
 	h1 , p {color: red;}
 </style>

Whenever we wanna style particular portion of our element then use span:
<style type="text/css">
	span {font-weight: bold;}
</style>
<p>today <span>is the</span> day </p>

